steps.
1.npm init(to initialize my app)
2.npm i express
3.npm i ejs.(Embedded Javascript which allow to generate HTML file)
4.npm i socket.io (Socket.IO is a library that enables real-time, bidirectional and event-based communication between the browser and the server.)
6.npm i uuid (used to create dinamic URL for each user)
7.npm i nodemon(allows automatically restarting the node application when file changes in the directory)
8.npm i -g peer.(PeerJS wraps the browser's WebRTC implementation to provide a complete, configurable, and easy-to-use peer-to-peer connection API)
DEPLOY
******
9.sign up heroku and (npm install -g heroku) already did it
10. Change the port 3001 to 443
11.create gitignore
12.git init 
13.git add .
14.git commit -m "ZOOM CLONE"
15. heroku create
16.git push heroku master
17. heroku ps:scale web=1
18. heroku open

